				 Comrades talk tough
																								New Delhi, Oct. 4 (PTI): Left parties today ruled out any reconciliation on the nuclear deal till the Centre puts it on hold and said their support should not be taken for granted.																								On the eve of a meeting of the joint mechanism on the deal, the Left also sent a note to the UPA on their concerns over the implications of Americas Hyde Act on Indias foreign and security policies.																								The government had earlier sent its views on various points raised by the Left at a meeting held on September 19.																								CPI leader A.B. Bardhan said UPA chief Sonia Gandhis comment in New York indicated that the government would go ahead with the deal. 																								Sonia had said the Lefts concerns were not a cause for alarm. Bardhan also warned the UPA not to take its differences with the Left lightly. 
